  "runtimeMin": 92,
  "format": "Sean and Amanda review Steven Soderbergh's ‘Magic Mike's Last Dance,' detour through his culture diary, and each count down a top five: Amanda's ‘ballet trash,' Sean's dance movies.",
  "segments": [
    {
      "kind": "discussion",
      "heading": "The ‘Air' Trailer",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Air",
          "year": 2023,
          "note": "Ben Affleck's Nike-Jordan movie, just trailered. Amanda: \"Emily in Paris for boys.\" Matt Damon plays Sonny Vaccaro; Viola Davis is Jordan's mother."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "review",
      "heading": "‘Magic Mike's Last Dance'",
      "note": "Soderbergh's stripper trilogy, part three",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Magic Mike's Last Dance",
          "year": 2023,
          "note": "Written by Reid Carolin, Channing Tatum back as Mike Lane, Salma Hayek Pinault replacing the originally cast Thandiwe Newton. A process movie about putting on a show; both hosts land on it as the least of the three but had a good time."
        },
        {
          "title": "Magic Mike",
          "year": 2012,
          "note": "Sean's pick as the best of the three: a McConaughey-driven, post-crash movie about service work that he calls Soderbergh's ‘Singin' in the Rain.' No. 4 on their Soderbergh rankings."
        },
        {
          "title": "Magic Mike XXL",
          "year": 2015,
          "note": "The hangout sequel (directed by Gregory Jacobs, shot and cut by Soderbergh) that's grown in reputation, thanks to the Manganiello convenience-store set piece and the big finale."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "discussion",
      "heading": "Late-Period Soderbergh",
      "note": "four in a row for Warner Bros.",
      "films": [
        {
          "title": "Let Them All Talk",
          "year": 2020,
          "note": "Meryl Streep, Candice Bergen and Dianne Wiest on the Queen Mary 2."
        },
        {
          "title": "No Sudden Move",
          "year": 2021,
          "note": "The one they think they underrated: a tighter, more cooked genre piece written by Ed Solomon."
        },
        {
          "title": "Kimi",
          "year": 2022,
          "note": "Both liked it more looking back; Sean caught it on HBO Max around his son's birth."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "discussion",
